description.plain: Mobile, Alabama rapper Yung Bleu (oftentimes stylized as BLEU) has grown a steady buzz thanks to his Investments mixtape series. After developing a working relationship with Boosie Badazz, Bleu landed a deal on Boosie’s Columbia Records imprint, Badazz Music Syndicate.

songs.full_title: You're Mines Still (Remix) by Yung Bleu (Ft. Drake)
songs.title: You’re Mines Still (Remix)

description.plain:
The remix to Yung Bleu’s melodic song “You’re Mines Still” was first teased on October 13, 2020 when Yung Bleu shared a now-deleted screenshot of his text conversation with Drake discussing the remix and Drake recording his verse.

Two days later, on October 15, 2020, the remix was leaked online. Therefore, Yung Bleu decided to release it on streaming platforms at 11:30pm the same day, thirty minutes before the rest of the deluxe for his October 2020 EP Love Scars: The 5 Stages of Emotions was released.

Keeping the theme of the original song, Bleu and Drake delve into their feelings for their ex-girlfriends.
